KPMG also said it would also hire an independent consultant to assess the firm’s ethics and integrity controls as well as its compliance, the SEC said in a statement. WASHINGTON - Accounting firm KPMG LLC has admitted to using stolen information to alter some of its previous audit work and cheating on training exams, and agreed to pay a $50 million penalty, the Securities and Exchange Commission said on Monday. KPMG also said it would also hire an independent consultant to assess the firm’s ethics and integrity controls as well as its compliance, the SEC said in a statement.